Thus, there must be a fine-tuning between the brane 
tension and the bulk cosmological constant  for 
static solutions to exist.  In this section we will discuss the
cosmology of this model in detail. 

Einstein's equations on the brane 
There are two ways of  deriving  the cosmological equations and 
we will describe both of them below. The first one is rather 
simple and makes use of the bulk equations only. The second 
method uses the  geometrical relationship between four-dimensoinal 
and five-dimensional quantities. 
We begin with the simpler method.

