cosmological solutions below, we will assume that this term 
is negligible.

The evolution of the scalar field is driven by two effects. First
of all, the scalar field couples to the trace of the energy 
momentum tensor via the gradient of . Secondly, the field is 
driven by the gradient of the potential , which might not 
necessarily vanish. 

